The article announces several nominations and appointments to the United States Sentencing Commission. Henry E. Hudson of Virginia is nominated to be a Member of the Commission, replacing Dabney Langhorne Friedrich. William Graham Otis of Virginia is also nominated to be a Member of the Commission, replacing Patti B. Saris. William H. Pryor Jr. of Alabama is nominated for reappointment as a Member of the Commission and also to be the Chair, replacing Patti B. Saris. Luis Felipe Restrepo of Pennsylvania is nominated to be a Member of the Commission, replacing Ketanji Brown Jackson.